    = yield
    #myModal.modal.hide.fade
      .modal-header
        %button.close{"aria-hidden" => "true", "data-dismiss" => "modal", :type => "button"} Ã—
        %h3{:style => "color: black;"} What Do the Colors Mean?
      .modal-body
        %p To Explain the colors here is a rhyeme:
        %blockquote
          %p
            Weather Beacon
            = succeed "," do
              %b
                %span{:style => "color: red;"} red
            warmer weather is ahead.
          %p
            Weather Beacon
            = succeed "," do
              %b white
            colder weather is in sight.
          %p
            Weather Beacon
            = succeed "," do
              %b
                %span{:style => "color:green;"} green
            no change in temperature foreseen.
          %p
            Weather Beacon
            %b
              %span.flash flashing
            night or day, precipitation is on the way
          %p
        %p
          Thanks to #{link_to "KCCI, Des Moines", 'http://kcci.com', target: '_blank'}, for the rhyme.
        %p
          In case you need some video reminders about it here are some:
        %p
          Rocking the Full '80's look #{link_to "here is the rhyme on video", "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7P3vRWWFaD0"}.
        %p
          Weather Infomation is provided by: #{link_to "wunderground.com", "http://www.wunderground.com"}
      .modal-footer
        %a.btn.btn-primary{"aria-hidden" => "true", "data-dismiss" => "modal", :href => "#"} Close
